The Dutch police authorities have arrested eight suspects concerning the killing of the famous film maker Theo van Gogh.
A Dutch filmmaker who received death threats after his recent movie criticized the way women were treated under Islam, was shot and stabbed to death in Amsterdam
Some 20,000 people gathered in Amsterdam late to pay homage to controversial Dutch filmmaker and columnist Theo van Gogh who was murdered in the street.
As the nation reeled from another daylight killing following the assassination of outspoken politician Pim Fortuyn in 2002, Dutch Prime Minister Jan Peter Balkenende condemned the attack.
